# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1882-troy-trojans-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1879-troy-trojans-season] The 1879 season was the National League debut for the **Troy Trojans**.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1879-troy-trojans-season] They finished the season 19–56, last in the league.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1880-troy-trojans-season] The **1880 Troy Trojans** improved slightly from the previous season, finishing with a 41–42 record and in 4th place in the National League.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1881-troy-trojans-season] The **1881 Troy Trojans** finished in 5th place in the National League with a 39–45 record.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-boston-red-caps-season] The **1882 Boston Red Caps season** was the 12th season of the franchise.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-boston-red-caps-season] The Red Caps were a team in transition, as co-founder and longtime manager Harry Wright left the team and was replaced by John Morrill.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-buffalo-bisons-season] The **1882 Buffalo Bisons** finished the season with a 45–39 record, good for third place in the National League.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1882 Chicago White Stockings season** was the 11th season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the seventh in the National League and the fifth at Lakefront Park.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 55–29, 3 games ahead of the second place Providence Grays.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-troy-trojans-season] The 1882 season was to be the last for the **Troy Trojans**.
[src:1882-troy-trojans-season/1882-troy-trojans-season] The team finished at 35–48, in seventh place in the National League, and were disbanded after the season.
